  requirements for a sleep questionnaire application. The agent approached this
  by first surveying the existing  directory to understand the available
  files. It identified key source documents like  and
  , while noting that binary files (, ) could not be
  directly processed. The agent then systematically organized the project by
  creating a  directory and moving all original source
  files there. Subsequently, it created two new, comprehensive Markdown
  documents: , which outlines the product overview,
  functional, technical, and report generation requirements, and
  , which details the entire questionnaire
  structure, including specific questions, conditional logic, scoring
  mechanisms, and diagnostic criteria. This approach successfully transformed
  raw communications into a well-organized and actionable set of application
  requirements and specifications."
